{"questionId":"9071566","questionHtml":"<p>Formulate an equation that shows how aqueous carbon dioxide produces hydrogen&nbsp;ions, H<sup>+</sup>(aq).</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>CO<sub>2</sub>(aq) +&nbsp;H<sub>2</sub>O(l) <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp;H<sup>+</sup>(aq) +&nbsp;HCO<sub>3</sub><sup>–</sup>(aq)</p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p>CO<sub>2</sub>(aq) +&nbsp;H<sub>2</sub>O(l) <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span> H<sub>2</sub>CO<sub>3</sub>(aq) <strong><em>AND </em></strong>H<sub>2</sub>CO<sub>3</sub>(aq) <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span> H<sup>+</sup>(aq) +&nbsp;HCO<sub>3</sub><sup>–</sup>(aq)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept CO</em><sub><em>2</em></sub><em>(aq) +</em><em>&nbsp;</em><em>H</em><sub><em>2</em></sub><em>O(l) </em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span><em> 2H<sup>+</sup></em><em>(aq)&nbsp;</em><em>+&nbsp;</em><em>CO</em><em><sub>3</sub><sup>2–</sup></em><em>(aq).</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept equations with single arrow.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9071566","referenceCode":"18M.3.sl.TZ1.b","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Formulate an equation that shows how aqueous carbon dioxide produces hydrogen ions, H+(aq).","paper":"3","level":"sl","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","C: Energy","C.5 Environmental impact—global warming","Options","C: Energy"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}